1514.question: How much performance improvements they achieve on SQuAD?
1514.response: {'Answer': 'The Stochastic Answer Network (SAN) achieves an Exact Match (EM) score of 76.235 and an F1 score of 84.056 on the SQuAD dataset as seen in Table 1. This appears to be the best performance among the different architectures compared in that table.'}
1514.answer: Compared to baselines SAN (Table 1) shows  improvement of 1.096% on EM and 0.689% F1. Compared to other published SQuAD results (Table 2) SAN is ranked second.
